model.metaheuristic.experiment.util

Class ExperimentAlgorithm<S extends Solution<?>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.metaheuristic.experiment.util.ExperimentAlgorithm<S>

  • public final class ExperimentAlgorithm<S extends Solution<?>>
extends Object
    Class defining tasks for the execution of algorithms in parallel.


    The method runASingleStepOfAlgorithm() run the algorithm step by step.

      • prepareToRun

        public void prepareToRun(@NotNull
                         @NotNull Experiment<?> experimentData)
        Create a output directory to save the result of execution of algorithm using saveSolutionList(). So you have to call this method before call saveSolutionList().
        Parameters:
        experimentData - the experiment data.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if experiment base directory set up in experimentData is a empty string.

      • runASingleStepOfAlgorithm

        public void runASingleStepOfAlgorithm()
                               throws epanet.core.EpanetException,
                                      Exception
        Run a single step of algorithm.
        Throws:
        epanet.core.EpanetException - if algorithm execution has a problem with simulation
        Exception - if algorithm can't close the resource

      • saveSolutionList

        public void saveSolutionList()
                      throws FileNotFoundException,
                             IOException
        Save the solution of the algorithm in the directory configure for prepareToRun(model.metaheuristic.experiment.Experiment<?>). So you has to call first to prepareToRun(model.metaheuristic.experiment.Experiment<?>).
        Throws:
        IOException - If an I/O error occurs
        FileNotFoundException - if the file exists but is a directory rather than a regular file, does not exist but can not be created, or cannot be opened for any other reason.
        IllegalStateException - if prepareToRun has not been called or algorithm is not over (algorithmHasANextStep() is true).

      • getResult

        @NotNull
public @NotNull List<? extends Solution<?>> getResult()
        Return the result of this experiment algorithm.

        If the problem was a single objective the result should be a list with one solution. However if the problem was multiobjective the solution should be a list with the pareto front.

        Returns:
        the result.
